# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Normally, leave it uncommented.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you do not want it:
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Poetry uses pyproject.toml to manage dependencies, but recommends committing poetry.lock
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
.pdm.toml
#   and local settings in .pdm-python.path
